          "disabled": true,
          "settings": {
            "title": "Shipping"
          }
        },
        "question_adqrYK": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Will it really help stop my snoring?",
            "answer": "<p>If your snoring is caused by restricted nasal airflow — which is the most common cause — then yes! By gently opening your nasal passages, the dilator lets air flow freely, which significantly reduces or even stops snoring for most users. Many customers notice a difference from the very first night.</p>"
          }
        },
        "question_TDP7NK": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Is it comfortable to wear all night?",
            "answer": "<p>Absolutely. It's made from soft, flexible, skin-safe material that molds gently to your nose, so most people forget they're even wearing it after a few minutes. If you're new to nasal dilators, start with the medium size and adjust from there — comfort is the goal.</p>"
          }
        },
        "question_hPGXCN": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "What sizes are included, and how do I pick the right one?",
            "answer": "<p><br/>Every pack includes 3 sizes — Small, Medium, and Large — so you can find your perfect fit. We recommend starting with Medium. If it feels too tight, go down to Small. If it slips out or feels loose, try Large. You're guaranteed to find the one that works for you.<br/><br/></p>"
          }
        },
        "question_7Rxwez": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "How do I clean it?",
            "answer": "<p><br/>Super simple. Just rinse it with warm water and mild soap after each use, and let it air dry. Once a week, soak it in warm soapy water for a few minutes for a deeper clean. That's all the maintenance it needs — it's fully reusable for months.<br/><br/></p>"
          }
        },
        "question_Pzgd7t": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Is it safe to use every night?",
            "answer": "<p><br/><br/>Yes! The nasal dilator is drug-free, non-invasive, and made from safe, medical-grade materials. There are no side effects, and it's designed for nightly use. That said, if you have any specific nasal conditions or recent nose surgery, check with your doctor before using it.<br/><br/></p>"
          }
        }
      },
